"{\"uid\": \"promptnewsonline.com-botswana-declares-half-day-holiday-to-celebrate-first-olympic-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Botswana has declared half-day public holiday to celebrate its first-ever Olympic gold medal, following athlete Letsile Tebogo's victory.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999509652765, \"rank\": 4.9034699424764843e-08, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gold medal was won at the men's 200m sprint final at the ongoing 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Botswanan President Mokgweetsi Masisi announced to the nation that he has found it a fitting tribute to Tebogo, \\\"Botswana's Sensation,\\\" to grant Batswana and residents an afternoon off on this very day.\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 250, \"end\": 267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mokgweetsi Masisi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\"}, {\"begin\": 343, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999509652765, \"rank\": 4.9034699424764843e-08, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 354, \"end\": 363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTC_Sensation\", \"score\": 0.9963305368716995, \"rank\": 0.003682579145281376, \"text\": \"Sensation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTC_Sensation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTC_Sensation\"}, {\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.97651292742887e-13, \"text\": \"Batswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Permanent Secretary to the President Emmah Peloetletse said in a statement released on Friday.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision was made to recognise and honor Tebogo, who has become the first African to win a gold medal in the 200m event in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement described Tebogo's performance and achievement as \\\"markedly outstanding and deserving of the nation to celebrate him in a most unique and responsible manner that will etched in the history of the country.\\\"\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old athlete secured Botswana's first gold medal of the Paris Olympics by completing the 200m sprint in 19.46 seconds on Thursday.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999509652765, \"rank\": 4.9034699424764843e-08, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This marks Botswana's first Olympic gold medal, following its first-ever Olympic medal in 2012 when Nigel Amos won silver in the 800m, and the men's 4\\u00d7400 relay squad won bronze at the Tokyo 2020 Games.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1050, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999509652765, \"rank\": 4.9034699424764843e-08, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://d